At that time, among the disciples of the Great Purity era who stood in attendance, I witnessed these events with my own eyes. Master Situ had repeatedly pledged to inscribe the rites of enfeoffment upon metal and stone, yet before he could fulfill this, he had already ascended as an immortal. When I, Great Purity, assumed the humble post at the lower abode, I long contemplated carrying on his unfulfilled intent, but pressing affairs left no leisure for the task.

In the spring of the dingmao year, the *Inner Transmission* and its *Continuation* were fortunately completed. My fellow disciples of the same rank once again expressed concern that the rites of enfeoffment remained unrecorded, saying: "Without their inscription, not only will the numinous marvels of the Three Lords and the august reverence of the sacred court fail to be proclaimed, but neither will it be seen how we of Kongshan have magnified the pulse of this Dao and expounded its transmission." Thereupon, I received this charge with the utmost reverence and now dutifully inscribe this to mark the time.

On the full moon of the third month in the dingmao year,
The Specially Bestowed Master of Pure Tranquility, Illuminating Perfection, and Subtle Wonder;
Specially Appointed Daoist Rectifier of the Maoshan Mountain Gate;
Provisional Supervisor of the Chongxi Abbey before the Throne and Overseer of All Abbeys on This Mountain;
Purple-Robed Zhang Dachun respectfully inscribes.

*Enfeoffment Rites for the Three Mao Lords, Volume the First*
The Specially Bestowed Master of the Cavernous Mystery, Supervisor of the Right Bureau, and Director of Daoist Affairs
Minister Situ Shitan, the High Scholar of the Void-White Studio at the Yousheng Abbey, reverently undertakes this charge.

The Specially Bestowed Master of Pure Tranquility, Illuminating Perfection, and Subtle Wonder;
Specially Appointed Daoist Rectifier of the Maoshan Mountain Gate;
Provisional Supervisor of the Chongxi Abbey and Overseer of All Abbeys on This Mountain;
Purple-Robed Minister Zhang Dachun, compiler.

Issued by the Ministry of Rites on the first day of the first month in the ninth year of the Chunyou era.

On the first day of the first month, the imperial edict was reverently received, bestowing a decree of exhortation:
"The High Scholar of the Void-White Studio, Master of the Cavernous Mystery, Situ Shitan, is hereby specially promoted to Registrar of the Left Bureau and Director of Daoist Affairs."

The Right Bureau has duly noted this for Minister Situ Shitan.
First day of the first month in the ninth year of the Chunyou era.
Imperial Decree.
